Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(halved).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and sliced). Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

When the pan is hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Lower the heat slightly, then stir in the tomatoes, onion and a knob of @?butter{knob} (if you have any). Add a drizzle of @?oil{drizzle} if it's a little dry, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cover with a #lid{} or #foil{}, then cook, stirring occasionally, until the onions and tomatoes have softened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @spaghetti{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some of the pasta water, @reserved pasta water{150%ml} (see ingredients for amount), then drain the pasta in a #colander{}.

Pop back into the pan, drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the veg has softened, remove the lid from the frying pan and stir in the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, a small pinch of @chilli flakes{1%small pinch} (add less if you don't like heat) and @red wine vinegar{12%ml}.

Bring to the boil, cook for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in the reserved pasta water and bring back to the boil.

Stir the @king prawns{150%g} into the sauce and cook for another ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Taste and season with more @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add some more @?chilli flakes{} if you'd like some more heat.

Once the prawns are cooked, add the cooked spaghetti to the sauce and toss together well.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if needed.

Remove from the heat, then stir through the chives. Divide the prawn spaghetti between your bowls and serve.

Enjoy!